    "text": "The palace of the Counts of Miranda in Peñaranda de Duero is a significant example of Spanish Renaissance architecture from the 16th century, blending Gothic, Hispano-Islamic, and emerging Renaissance styles.",
    "topic": "Palace of Peñaranda de Duero"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Spanish Renaissance, particularly in the Iberian Peninsula, has been underappreciated due to its hybrid nature combining multiple architectural traditions.",
    "topic": "Spanish Renaissance"
  },
  {
    "text": "Main rooms and coffered ceilings are key features defining the noble palace model in Renaissance Spain, as exemplified by the palace of Peñaranda de Duero.",
    "topic": "Noble palace model"
  },
  {
    "text": "The palace of the Counts of Miranda in Peñaranda de Duero demonstrates a harmonious coexistence of Gothic, Hispano-Islamic, and Renaissance architectural elements.",
    "topic": "Architectural fusion"
  },
  {
    "text": "Studying palatial works like the one in Peñaranda de Duero aims to deepen the understanding of the Spanish Renaissance and its hybrid architectural influences.",
